        <h3 class="heading">Skills</h3>
        <p>C, C++(OpenMP,CUDA,MPI) ,Java, Apache Spark, OSX, Linux, Windows Android, OpenGL, OpenCV, openFrameworks, Python, Caffe, Caffe2, Chainer, ChainerMN</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <h3 class="heading">Researches</h3>
        <ol>
          <li> Accelerating Matrix Multiplication in Deep Learning by using Low-Rank Approximation<br>
            The time required for learning and inference of the convolutional neural network used in the field of image recognition of deep learning is mostly occupied by the convolution operation and it is put into the problem of calculating two large dense matrix products by a method called im2col.<br>
            Focusing on the characteristic  of noise tolerance in convolutional neural networks, The method to reduce size  and reduce computational complexity by reducing low-ranking dense matrices  achieves to speed up learning and inference.<br>
          <br>
          </li>
          <li>Accelerating Convolutional Neural Networks Using Low Precision Arithmetic<br>
            Reducing memory consumption and calculation time is expected by changing the whole operation of the convolution neural network and the model of the network from single precision to half precision.<br>
            The out-of-core problem such that the model size of the network is large and do not get on the device memory of the GPU was solved. <br>
            Furthermore low precision learning achieves to speed up memory access such as fully-connected layer which is memory-access-bound and achieves to improve throughput such as convolution layer which is  computation-bound by SIMD instruction.<br>
            Regarding the method of quantizing to 8-bit, we also examine the quantization method and the influence on recognition accuracy / computation time.<br>
          <br>
          </li>
          <li>Investigation of Optimization Method of Deep Learning in a Large Scale Parallel Environment<br>
            The supervised DNN learning come down to the minimization problem of the function representing the error between the training data and the supervised label.<br>
            Conventionally, the stochastic gradient descent method (SGD), which is an on-line gradient descent method, has been used, but due to the increase in batch size due to large-scale parallelization, it is known that the smoothing due to the noise of the minimizing loss function is lost and tends to converge to a local optimal solution with low generalization performance.<br>
            On the other hand, the natural gradient method (NGD) which adopts the Fisher information matrix as the Riemannian metric by considering the parameter of DNN as the point on the Riemann space has drawn attention as an effective solution in DNN learning.<br>
          In this research, we consider an optimization method suitable for parallelization with high convergence performance using approximate calculation of Fischer information matrix with high calculation cost.</li>
        </ol>
